#compdef linky
# =============================================================================
# linky — Boris Krywoltzky's "CLI tool to retrieve Linky smart
#         meters data" — a Node.js CLI for fetching electricity
#         consumption + production data from French Enedis smart
#         meters (Linky brand) via the public Enedis API.
#         Distinguishing from EnedisAPI direct usage, RTE Eco2mix
#         dashboards, and other French electricity data tools by:
#           - SINGLE-BINARY FRENCH SMART-METER CLIENT — designed
#             specifically for the Enedis (French national grid)
#             API + Linky smart meters deployed in 30+ million
#             French households
#           - 6 DATA-RETRIEVAL SUBCOMMANDS:
#               linky daily            Daily consumption (kWh)
#               linky loadcurve        30-min load curve (W)
#               linky maxpower         Daily max consumption (VA)
#               linky dailyprod        Daily production (solar)
#               linky loadcurveprod    30-min production curve
#               linky auth             Connect via Enedis token
#           - AUTH-TOKEN PERSISTENCE via Conf — `linky auth
#             --token TOKEN` stores the token to ~/.config/linky/
#             config.json (XDG-compliant); subsequent commands
#             auto-use the stored token unless --token overrides
#           - 3 OUTPUT FORMATS: --format pretty (default,
#             colorized table via chalk) / json (machine-readable)
#             / csv (spreadsheet-compatible)
#           - DATE-RANGE QUERYING: --start (default yesterday) +
#             --end (default today) with dayjs parsing of
#             AAAA-MM-JJ format (YYYY-MM-DD)
#           - PRM SELECTION via --prm — when an Enedis token has
#             access to multiple metering points (PRMs), this
#             flag picks one; auto-detected if only one PRM
#           - UPDATE-NOTIFICATIONS via update-notifier — checks
#             npm registry for new linky versions, displays
#             upgrade message
#           - QUIET MODE via --quiet — suppresses ora spinner
#             animations + progress messages (suitable for cron
#             jobs / scripts)
#         Used by: French solar producers tracking daily
#         production, energy-efficiency analysts monitoring
#         consumption patterns, home automation enthusiasts
#         integrating Linky data into Home Assistant / openHAB /
#         Domoticz, and as a reference implementation of the
#         meow + ora + chalk + conf TypeScript CLI stack.
#
# Author:  Boris Krywoltzky (bokub on GitHub) — French Node.js
#          developer, also author of conso.boris.sh (the token
#          provisioning service linky uses).  License: MIT.
# Source:  https://github.com/bokub/linky
#          https://github.com/bokub/linky/blob/master/bin/cli.ts
#          https://github.com/bokub/linky/blob/master/bin/store.ts
# CLI:     bin/cli.ts — uses meow for argument parsing +
#          subcommand dispatch via switch on cli.input[0].
#          bin/store.ts uses Conf for persistent auth-token
#          storage.  Headline library: **conf** (meow + chalk +
#          ora are well-documented across many Node completions;
#          conf is the new variant being documented here,
#          expanding Axis 13 to 2 TS-Node entries).
# Library: conf (https://github.com/sindresorhus/conf)
#          ("conf" — Sindre Sorhus (sindresorhus on GitHub, also
#           author of chalk + ora + wrap-ansi R627 + ~1500 other
#           npm packages) — released 2016 as "Simple config
#           handling for your app or module".  Distinct from
#           cosmiconfig (R631, the Node Axis 13 opener) by being:
#             1. FIXED-LOCATION PERSISTENT JSON STORE — where
#                cosmiconfig DISCOVERS read-only config files,
#                conf MAINTAINS a read/write JSON store at a
#                FIXED LOCATION on disk (XDG-compliant on Linux,
#                ~/Library/Application Support/ on macOS, %APPDATA%
#                on Windows) via the env-paths package
#             2. PROJECT-AWARE PATHS — `new Conf({ projectName:
#                'myapp' })` automatically resolves to:
#                  - Linux:   $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/myapp/config.json
#                  - macOS:   ~/Library/Preferences/myapp/config.json
#                  - Windows: %APPDATA%/myapp/Config/config.json
#             3. TYPESCRIPT-FIRST API — conf v10+ ships with
#                strict TypeScript types via generic StoreType
#                parameter:
#                  type StoreType = { token: string; prm?: string };
#                  const store = new Conf<StoreType>({ projectName: 'myapp' });
#                  store.set('token', 'abc');  // type-checked
#             4. SCHEMA VALIDATION via JSON Schema — `new Conf({
#                schema: { token: { type: 'string' } } })`
#                validates writes against a JSON Schema
#             5. ENCRYPTION via encryptionKey — opaque
#                encryption-at-rest for sensitive values like
#                API tokens (linky uses this pattern)
#             6. MIGRATIONS — `migrations: { '>=2.0.0': (store)
#                => store.clear() }` lets the library define
#                schema migrations across version upgrades
#             7. SINDRE-SORHUS ECOSYSTEM PROVENANCE — Sindre is
#                the author of 1500+ npm packages including
#                chalk (3.5B weekly downloads), ora (40M weekly),
#                wrap-ansi (R627, 3.5B weekly), pretty-bytes,
#                pretty-ms, execa, got, query-string, and many
#                others; conf is part of his "production
#                infrastructure" library family)
# License: MIT (linky); MIT (conf)
# Status:  linky — 283+ stars on bokub/linky, widely used in
#          French smart-meter monitoring; conf — 1,341+ stars
#          on sindresorhus/conf, ~6M weekly npm downloads,
#          foundational dependency of Electron apps + many
#          desktop tooling utilities + stepci/stepci (1.9k
#          stars) + ginobefun/BestBlogs (3.7k stars) + uetchy/
#          github-social + kognise/crypticat + jschuur/
#          localtime-cli + bokub/linky (THIS) + BearStudio/
#          create-start-ui + Neurall-build/implit + 600+ Node.js
#          CLIs that need persistent JSON state.
#
